The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Knight Club planned
                                                                                                                       7                                      Knight Club planned
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) on Saturday announced plans to launch its Knight Club.         
	This will be an unique opportunity for fans to come together as a community and support their team.         
	On becoming an official Knight, members will receive a gift pack containing a welcome letter from owners Shah Rukh Khan, Juhi Chawla and Jay Mehta, a KKR membership card with an exclusive number, a KKR sling bag, a KKR T-shirt, a KKR key chain and many more such gift items.         
	Members will also have access to exclusive content, competitions and discounts on KKR merchandise.         
	All this will be available for just Rs 550 a year!         
	On-spot registration will be available at the Eden Gardens during the India versus South Africa second Test, beginning on Sunday.         
	Online registration can also be done by simply logging on to www.kkr.in, or by mailing to theknightclubkkr.in         
	Its an opportunity of a lifetime and a chance to join the biggest screaming army in the world!                                                                                                                     
